{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, the high accuracy score of 0.98 reflects the overall rate at which the model makes correct predictions for both positive and negative classes.",
    "This balanced performance is mirrored in the weighted F1-score, which is the harmonic mean of precision and recall, indicating that the model maintains a strong balance between precision and recall across all classes.",
    "Finally, an AUC-ROC score of 0.99 indicates an excellent ability of the model to discriminate between the positive and negative classes.",
    "A score close to 1.0 means that the model has a high true-positive rate and a low false-positive rate across different thresholds.",
    "In comparison to the FAST-RNN model, the other DLbased models like LSTM, GRU, and CNN-LSTM also show robust performance with all metrics ranging from 0.96 to 0.97."
  ]
}